Here is a capture of the AUXCH data during the link standup.

This was made by bringing the AUXCH_IN signal to an I/O pin
and then capturing the stream with a Seleae Logic analyser.

It can be decoded with the Manchester protocol decoder, with
MSB first option, and a data rate of 1Mb/s.

Note that some of the replies (when all zeros) were not 
decoded by the logic analyser I was using - they do not have
timestamps
